said that it did.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">However, rather than using the number of homes the scheme is helping, I should have used the overall number of ne</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">w build homes in total. Last year, 22 of the largest builders singed up to Help to Buy and built around 61,500 homes. For these builders, an increase in 10-20% would represent 6,000 to 12,000 homes a year. The overall number may be higher still, given ther</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e is now a total of 939 house builders that have registered for the scheme.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Please feel free to contact me should you require any further information.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">7 November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>